WEBVTT

00:07.751 --> 00:08.912
[door opens]

00:09.514 --> 00:10.823
<i>Maura.</i>

00:11.418 --> 00:14.410
- Sweetheart.
- Good morning, Angela.

00:14.444 --> 00:17.246
- Hi.
- How you doing?

00:17.314 --> 00:20.716
Oh, I don't know.

00:20.784 --> 00:25.654
- [sighs] I don't know.
- Go ahead, Maura. Let it out.

00:27.090 --> 00:30.159
I'll get us some coffee.

00:30.193 --> 00:35.130
A tragic accident like that...

00:35.165 --> 00:38.033
you never really see it coming.

00:39.836 --> 00:42.938
[inhales deeply]
I am worried about Jane.

00:42.972 --> 00:45.774
Her and Barry were so close, and...

00:45.842 --> 00:48.310
well, with the pregnancy
and all those hormones ...

00:48.378 --> 00:49.778
Shh! Shh.

00:49.846 --> 00:51.347
Jane doesn't know that you know

00:51.381 --> 00:53.749
and she hasn't told anyone
else, so you need to just ...

00:53.783 --> 00:56.419
I know.
Keep my trap shut. I will.

00:56.586 --> 00:58.821
Doesn't mean that a mother can't worry.

00:58.855 --> 01:01.991
She's always been so good
about sympathizing with others.

01:02.025 --> 01:05.861
But when it comes to her own feelings,
she bottles everything up.

01:05.929 --> 01:09.598
She needs to let it out.
So do you.

01:09.633 --> 01:12.601
You need a good cry, a big cry.

01:12.669 --> 01:14.503
We will. In time.

01:14.538 --> 01:17.606
- Dabda.
- Gesundheit?

01:17.641 --> 01:22.778
The stages of grief.
Denial, anger, bargaining,

01:22.812 --> 01:24.613
depression, acceptance.

01:24.648 --> 01:26.749
It's from Elisabeth
Kubler-Ross' seminal work

01:26.783 --> 01:28.851
in the mid-20th century.

01:28.885 --> 01:30.619
Though current research
shows that yearning

01:30.654 --> 01:32.988
is actually a more accurate
expression of the final ...

01:33.023 --> 01:36.192
Okay. That all sounds great.
When's the crying start?

01:38.195 --> 01:41.597
- Hey. Morning, Ma.
- Hi, honey.

01:43.200 --> 01:45.034
Thanks for letting me
stay over last night.

01:45.068 --> 01:47.636
No problem. I didn't
want to be alone, either.

01:47.671 --> 01:50.906
- Where you going?
- To the station.

01:50.941 --> 01:52.608
Don't you think it would be better

01:52.642 --> 01:57.146
- to stay home and feel your feelings?
- Ma, he loved his work.

01:57.180 --> 01:59.915
He wouldn't want me to just
curl up and stop doing mine.

01:59.950 --> 02:01.917
I don't think that's what
your mom's suggesting.

02:01.952 --> 02:04.653
Maybe ... maybe you can sit
down, have a cup of coffee?

02:04.688 --> 02:06.789
<i>Real coffee.</i>

02:06.823 --> 02:10.292
- I can make us all some breakfast.
- I'll take the coffee.

02:10.327 --> 02:11.927
Oh, uh...

02:11.962 --> 02:16.765
Thanks.
See you later.

02:16.833 --> 02:20.002
- Wasn't that your vase?
- [door opens] Yep.

02:20.036 --> 02:23.072
Denial. [door closes]
Check.

02:23.106 --> 02:25.975
[sighs]

